summary: Day 11 - Slateport City 3:15 am. Future me will hit you up with some commentary and a change in how I’m going to be approaching...
caption:
Day 11 - Slateport City

3:15 am. Future me will hit you up with some commentary and a change in how I’m going to be approaching these. ‘Til then

[image description: a digital illustration of Lisia from pokemon taking a selfie with a nekomimi girl, Lisia’s altaria, and an espeon in front of some market stalls. The main hue is pink.]

Comments under the cut!

Thanks again for your patience! I had been looking forward to this one but life likes to get in the way. Its becoming more apparent that this was not a great formula for me to undertake for huevember. We’re two thirds through the month and I’m only just finishing the first third. I bit off more than I could chew ^u^;; 

I’m thinking that I’ll give huevember a rest. I’m reaching burnout and it’s not worth stressing myself out over a challenge. Plus I’m already going to go over November and would rather work on christmas stuff. I’ll still be attempting to complete the prompt list with restricted time for each picture and a main hue, but it’s not going to be a daily challenge, rather I’ll aim to have it completed before I return to uni. That’s the thing about challenges, sometimes you can’t complete them the way you wanted to and that’s ok! You still get the practice and possibly learn new things along the way. Mad props to everyone who does complete huevember though. Good on you!
